textContent: Jennifer is invited to be a bridesmaid at her old friend Lulu's wedding. When she arrives at the reception, however, she is disappointed to find that Lulu wants her to present as her normal self instead of being in her She-Hulk form, and is saddled with numerous pre-wedding duties. Things become more complicated when Titania shows up at the reception, as she is dating one of Lulu's groomsmen. Jennifer bonds with Josh Miller, a friend of the groom, before Titania attacks her, making it clear that she wants Jennifer out of the picture. Jennifer transforms into She-Hulk and they fight briefly, until Titania loses a few teeth and loses her cool before storming out. Meanwhile, Mallory and Nikki work on a divorce case for a superhuman individual known as "Mr. Immortal", who has gotten out of numerous previous marriages by repeatedly faking his own death, but the case becomes more difficult when eight of Mr. Immortal's previous spouses all file suits against him after discovering his secret thanks to an online video on a site called Intelligencia showing one of his feigned deaths. Nikki is able to resolve the case by helping all eight of the spouses to work out compensation deals. As she and Mallory discuss the aftermath of the case, however, they discover a message board of an organization on Intelligencia that contains numerous death threats aimed at She-Hulk. Meanwhile, the organization is ready to give another try to steal Jennifer's blood sample after the Wrecking Crew's failed attempt to do so.

Jennifer goes on several dates with Josh, but he disappears and seemingly ghosts her after they sleep together. While anticipating a text from him, she receives a call from Blonsky's parole officer Chuck Donelan, who informs her that the inhibitor that stops Blonsky from turning into Abomination is broken and that she has to go to his meditation retreat to check on him. When she arrives, Man-Bull and El Aguila accidentally destroy her car, forcing her to stay there until it can be towed away. Despite the retreat lacking internet and cell coverage, Jennifer continues to nervously await a response from Josh. She attends a group therapy session with Blonsky, Man-Bull, El Aguila, Porcupine, Saracen, and Wrecker of the Wrecking Crew, where she is convinced to delete Josh's contact information and let go of her feelings towards him. Three days earlier, Josh secretly copied the contents of Jennifer's phone onto his own, on the behalf of "HulkKing," after sleeping with her.

Jennifer takes on a new case, representing  Eugene Patilio who superhero name is Leap-Frog, who wishes to sue Luke Jacobson for having provided him a faulty supersuit. Jacobson is represented by Matt Murdock in court, and manages to win the case due to Eugene inadvertently revealing that he disobeyed Jacobson's instructions for using the suit. Afterwards, Eugeneo contacts Jennifer asking for help against an unknown assailant. Jennifer arrives and battles the assailant, who she discovers to be Matt as his superhero persona Daredevil. Matt reveals to Jennifer that Eugene kidnapped Jacobson, and the two work together to rescue the latter. Afterwards, Jennifer and Matt sleeps together at her home. The next night, Jennifer attends the Southern California Law Awards gala where she accepts the Female Lawyer of the Year award, but the gala is interrupted by an Intelligencia broadcast, which smears Jennifer' reputation by displaying footage of her in bed with Josh Miller. Jennifer goes into a rage and destroys the gala stage, then attempts to capture one of the Intelligencia member, but she is stopped by Department of Damage Control agents.

Jennifer is released from Damage Control custody, but is forced to wear an inhibitor to prevent her from transforming, and loses her job at GLK&H. Nikki and Pug infiltrate an Intelligencia event, where they learn that Phelps is HulkKing and Blonsky as the Abomination is serving as a motivational speaker. Walters arrives at the event and confronts Phelps, who injects himself with her blood and transforms into a Hulk. After Titania and Bruce unexpectedly appear in the ensuing fight, a confused Jennifer breaks the fourth wall to confront the show's writers in Marvel Studios: Assembled. She meets with K.E.V.I.N. an artificial intelligence that claims to be in charge of the Marvel Cinematic Universe's storyline decisions, and persuades it to rewrite the finale, to which it reluctantly agrees. Returning to her show, she finds Phelps and Blonsky have been arrested. While celebrating with her family and is now dating Matt. Bruce returns from Sakaar with his son Skaar. After regaining her job and being cleared of all charges, Jennifer vows to continue her work as a lawyer and a superhero. Meanwhile, Wong breaks Blonsky out of prison and takes him to Kamar-Taj.

Scott Lang life has been going pretty great. He is liked and respected in his hometown of San Francisco, and has even written a successful memoir. Things are also going well for his girlfriend and fellow Avenger Hope van Dyne, who now runs her own company and is using Pym Particles to help the world, as well as her parents Hank Pym and Janet van Dyne who are just happy to be reunited following Janet's thirty years trapped in the Quantum Realm although Janet still refuses to talk about her time there. The only bone of contention for Scott is that his Cassie, who is now living with him and Hope, has been arrested more than once due to her participation in protests. After Scott and Hope bail her out, the two have a mild argument where she accuses her father of enjoying his fame and not actually doing anything to help the world now it isn't under an immediate threat. She also accidentally implies during the conversation that she has her own super suit, although quickly tries to shrug it off when her father enquires further. They head to the Pym Residence to have dinner, and the conversation turns to a device that Cassie and Hank have been working on; a Quantum Satellite. They explain it's designed to try and send a signal into the Quantum Realm to try and establish communications. Janet freaks out when she realises that someone could send a signal back and demands it be shut down, however the device ends up imploding and sucking in the five, along with some ants that Hank had been experimenting on to increase their intelligent. The Pym family are separated from Scott and Cassie and land in a completely different part of the Quantum Realm to the two.

Scott manages to rescue Cassie from falling to her death before confronting an alliance named the Freedom Fighters as Hope and Hank are guided through the Quantum Realm by Janet, who later brings them to Axia to meet an old friend. Scott and Cassie perform a ritual to understand the Freedom Fighters' language, learning of a man who managed to conquer what was once the home of the Freedom Fighters. Upon meeting Janet's friend Krylar, Krylar has the ruler's guard attack Janet's relatives, leading them to escape in Krylar's Yacht. The Freedom Fighters are also soon under attack by the guard and M.O.D.O.K., whom Scott and Cassie find out is none other than Darren Cross, who is now deformed from the Yellowjacket suit's destruction and has been left with a massive head but tiny limbs necessitating him to use a hover chair. While Scott is arrested and forced to make a deal with the man named Kang, having to retrieve the Multiversal Power Core, Janet explains to Hope and Hank that Kang the Conqueror was a scientist also trapped in the Quantum Realm who attempted to fix his Time Chair, only to have Janet sabotage his departure because she realised from his ship's engine that he had destroyed several timelines and took countless lives, and hadn't actually crashed in the Quantum Realm as she'd assumed but was exiled there. As Ant-Man, Scott shrinks into the enlarged, blown up Multiversal Power Core, shrinking it with the Wasp's help. Because they rebel against him, Kang steals the Power Core from them, defeating Ant-Man and the Wasp and taking Van Dyne with him as M.O.D.O.K. crashes Hank's ship.

Kang explains his origin and his plan to thwart the Council of Kangs for exiling him to Janet as Cassie evades captivity and frees the Freedom Fighters. Ant-Man and the Wasp meet Hank, accompanied by the smarter ants who have also traveled to the Quantum Realm. Cassie interrupts Kang's transmission to Axia, telling all residents to fight against Kang. Telling M.O.D.O.K. to kill Cassie, Kang is confronted by Giant-Man, approaching Axia's center. The Freedom Fighters and the inhabitants of the Quantum Realm also help defeat Kang, despite losing to his attacks. Cassie is able to get the best of M.O.D.O.K. and tells Darren that he has the capacity to change and doesn't have to be a 'dick' all his life. With Ant-Man, the Wasp and Stature attempting to battle him, Hank calls his ants which had arrived in the Quantum Realm centuries before the humans and developed their own society to distract him. Convinced he has been acting horribly, Darren sacrifices his life as a hero in disabling Kang's forcefield he had made, allowing the ants to attack him with Scott uneasily declaring Darren an Avenger when Darren asks. Janet opens a portal back to Earth until Scott, the last person to return, was blasted away by Kang. Scott and Kang fight in a brutal hand-to-hand fight, Kang was sucked in by the distorting Power Core by Hope's help. Looking back at the celebrating Freedom Fighters, Scott and Hope leave the Quantum Realm.

Back home, Scott continues his happy life and orchestrates a fake surprise birthday for Cassie due to him missing so many. Scott briefly reflects on Kang's words and worries that he may not be dead or the door might now be open to the ones who exiled him, but decides not to dwell on that for now and focus on his extended family. Believing the exiled Kang has died, the Council of Kangs calls every Kang variant in the Multiverse. They discuss that the Avengers may have to be dealt with as they're not only touching the fabric of the Multiverse but were even able to seemingly kill one of their own. Sometime after in the 20th Century, Loki attends a presentation about time with Mobius M. Mobius. The presentation being that of Victor Timely's, Mobius isn't worried while Loki is terrified.

At Knowhere, Kraglin Obfonteri tells the Guardians of the Galaxy the story of how he and Peter Quill tried to celebrate Earth's Christmas when Peter was still a kid, however, Yondu Udonta got mad and told them to cut it out. Kraglin says that according to the multi-calendar, Christmas is coming but Nebula says that they have too much on their plate after buying Knowhere from The Collector and needing to rebuild it following Thanos' attack. Meanwhile, Quill gets approached by Bzermikitokolok who is researching Christmas and wrote a song about it but he ends up completely mischaracterizing it, to Peter's annoyance.

textContent: Mantis tells Drax that she wants to do something for Peter for Christmas, due to her secret that she is Ego's child and, therefore, Peter's sister. Thinking about giving him an unforgettable Christmas present, Drax suggests that Quill's hero, Kevin Bacon, would be a perfect option, so they take their spaceship The Bowie and fly to Earth. Walking across Los Angeles, Mantis and Drax get mistaken for cosplayers and earn a lot of money from tourists who wanted to take pictures with them. Looking for Bacon, Mantis and Drax go to the club where they get wasted, before the bystander gives them a star tours booklet with Bacon's home address. They go to Bacon's house and try to take him as a present but Bacon says that he cannot help them. However, Mantis and Drax then break into his house, so horrified Bacon calls the police and tries to run away. The police arrives but Mantis and Drax incapacitate the officers, before catching up to Bacon. Mantis uses her powers to put Bacon in a trance and convince him to go with them.

textContent: The Guardians of the Galaxy have been working to restore the Nowhere outpost following Thanos' attack, when they are attacked without warning by Adam Warlock, sent to capture Rocket. Although he fails in his task, Rocket is grievously injured and the Guardians find they’re unable to operate without triggering a kill switch implanted by the High Evolutionary. Quill blames himself for being in a drunken stupor when Adam arrived, having fallen into alcoholism after Gamora's death, and not reacting as quickly as he should have as a result. Mantis tries to talk with her brother about running from pain, also reminding him of his grandfather that might still be alive who has had to live with losing his daughter and never knowing what happened to his grandson. Adam returns to Ayesha, and it's revealed that the High Evolutionary had him removed from his cocoon early to capture Rocket. He threatens Ayesha with the destruction of the Sovereign race, which he created, if they fail to retrieve Rocket. Ayesha decides to send Adam to do the job himself to prove she can still be useful.

The Guardians find they must go to the Orgosphere, a medical outpost, to get the information they need to shut down the kill switch so they can perform the necessary medical treatments on Rocket, who will die otherwise. Nebula contacts the time-shifted version of Gamora for her assistance, as she has joined the Ravagers. Gamora leads the team into the Orgosphere, while Quill attempts to persuade her than they fell in love, something she refuses to believe as she has nothing but contempt for him. Despite causing a massive firefight on the station, they manage to escape with the file, with Drax and Nebula suffering injuries. Observing it, they see the horrific torture and operations Rocket was put through (with Nebula noting that her own painful mutilations at Thanos' hands doesn't compare with what Rocket suffered) but find the information they need is missing. They realise that Theel, one of the High Evolutionary's scientists, downloaded the information before deleting it and has it stored in memory.

The Guardians visit Counter-Earth, despite Gamora's warning of a trap. Ayesha and Adam capture a Ravager and his pet Blurp and tries to interrogate him of the Guardians' whereabouts, but Adam goes overboard when Ayesha tells him to make him realise they're serious and disintegrates him before they can ask more questions. The Sovereign intercepts a message from Gamora asking a Ravager outpost for pick up and follows the Guardians to Counter-Earth. Groot, Nebula, and Quill track down Theel's location. Nebula is refused entry for being a weapon herself. The High Evolutionary's captures Groot and Quill and sends a pig to the Guardian ship to retrieve Rocket. Gamora protects Rocket, but Adam arrives and kills the pig since he needs Rocket to save his own race, while Groot and Quill fight the High Evolutionary and his men using weapons hidden inside Groot. The High Evolutionary launches his spaceship/laboratory and destroys Counter-Earth in the process. Nebula, Drax and Mantis jump to the ship to try to save Groot and Quill, but unbeknownst to them, the two have jumped off the ship with Theel. Adam senses his mother is in danger, but arrives too late to save Ayesha as she and her ship are destroyed. Quill and Groot make it back to the ship and attempt to save Rocket, however it seems to be too late and he flatlines. Rocket suffers a near-death experience, experiencing a vision of Lylla, Teefs and Floor, who tell him it is not his time to go, just as Quill successfully overrides his kill switch and revives him.

Drax, Mantis and Nebula contact Quill and finds that he has escaped and that Rocket is alive. They also discover children in the High Evolutionary's ship. The three are captured and are to be fed to Abilisks. The Guardians come to their rescue with Kraglin Obfonteri's help. Mantis is able to communicate with the Abilisks and escapes with them. Using Cosmo's telekinesis, they connect the High Evolutionary's ship to Kraglin's ship to allow the children to cross. Drax decides to also rescue Adam, who was injured in one final desperate attempt to capture Rocket, telling him that everyone deserves a second chance. Rocket discovers baby raccoons and other animals in the ship. While trying to free them, Rocket is attacked by an obsessed High Evolutionary, but is rescued by the rest of the Guardians who all take the chance to lay a hit on him as payback for what he put Rocket through with Gamora delivering the coup-de-grace, pulling off his face in the process leaving behind only a bloody mess. The High Evolutionary, now in agonizing pain, tells Rocket to finish the job. Rocket however declines to kill him, deciding to be better than him, and the team is content to let the High Evolutionary suffer.

The Guardians rescue the rest of the experimented animals, but Cosmo succumbs to the strain of holding the ship together and collapses. Quill barely makes it out of the exploding ship and starts to freeze in space until he is rescued by Adam. Quill accepts that the Gamora he knew is gone and the one he knows now will never love him. Gamora bids him goodbye, admitting that she senses they could have been a 'fun' pair if things had been different, and returns to the Ravagers to be met with a triumphant welcome. Quill gathers the team and announces that he's decided to stop running and return home to Earth. Mantis also decides to leave; having spent her life either working for Ego or the Guardians she now intends to work out what she wants to do with her life. Nebula and Drax also leave the Guardians, having decided to turn Knowhere into a community and help raise the rescued children. Rocket believes that this means the Guardians of the Galaxy are finished, but Quill corrects him that they'll keep going without them and makes Rocket the leader. Mantis leaves with the Abilisks after waving farewell to Drax, who almost cries upon seeing her leave. Quill leaves Rocket his Microsoft Zune knowing Rocket enjoyed the music as much as he did, returns to Earth and reunites with his grandfather Jason Quill. At some point in that time, they have breakfast, with Jason reading a newspaper about Kevin Bacon's kidnapping during Christmas. Sometime later, Rocket is on Krylor with the new Guardians of the Galaxy, composed of Groot having grown larger, Adam, Cosmo, Phyla, Kraglin, and Blurp. As they all talk about their favorite music tastes, they are suddenly interrupted by monsters closing into the vicinity. Kraglin asks if they would like to have him deal with it, and Rocket replies that it would be faster if all of them join in. Phyla asks him if they should be sad about killing them, but Rocket says that someone needs to protect the Krylorians. As Cosmo asks Rocket to go "on their word", Rocket simply says "Word", and the Guardians charge into battle.

In Moscow, Talos pursues Everett K. Ross for killing CIA agent Prescod, who theorized that shapeshifting Skrull rebels, frustrated with the lack of progress of Talos and Nick Fury in finding them a new home, intend to incite war between Russia and the United States in order to take over the Earth. Maria Hill arrives to assist Ross and discovers that he is a Skrull in disguise. Hill calls Fury, who has been working in space following the Blip. Returning to Earth, Fury learns that Talos has been exiled from the Skrull Council and replaced by Gravik, who is leading the rebels. Fury is kidnapped by MI6 agents working for his old acquaintance Sonya Falsworth, who refuses to work with Fury to stop Gravik. Using a bug to eavesdrop on her and the UK prime minister, Fury and Talos locate another rebel who has provided dirty bombs to the rebels. One of these rebels is Talos's daughter G'iah, who was unaware that her mother Soren had been killed by the rebels. G'iah reveals the rebels' plan to attack Vossoyedineniye Square on Unity Day. Fury, Hill, and Talos attempt to intercept the bombs but are unable to stop Gravik from detonating them. In the ensuing chaos, Gravik disguises himself as Fury and kills Hill.

After escaping from the bombing attack, Fury learns from Talos that there are a million Skrulls living on Earth amongst the humans. An angered Fury parts way with Talos, and later meets with Hill's mother, Elizabeth, to explain the circumstances of her death. As the United States is implicated in the bombing attack, Gravik meets with members of the Skrull Council, who express disapproval of his actions. Gravik reminds the Council of Fury's failure to deliver on his promise, and appoints himself the new Skrull General with the majority in favor. Council member Shirley Sagar, who refuses to submit, secretly contacts Talos, who asks her to set up a meeting between him and Gravik. In London, Fury meets with Colonel James Rhodes and explains to him the Skrull threat. To Fury's dismay, Rhodes gives him a military discharge, due to his presence at the bombing attack which escalated the tension between the United States and other international governments. Falsworth arrives at a butcher shop, where one of the Skrulls, Brogan, is imprisoned, and interrogates him. She learns that Gravik is building a machine for the purpose of strengthening the Skrulls, and a scientist couple named Dalton is involved. G'iah secretly discovers that the Skrulls are experimenting on various alien samples. Afterwards, she accompanies Gravik on a mission to rescue Brogan. Suspecting him of having talked, Gravik has Brogan executed. Later, Fury returns to his home where he is greeted by his wife, Priscilla, who is secretly a Skrull.

Gravik reveals to the Skrull Council that he intends to create Super Skrulls using the collected foreign DNA, and that he has sent rebels to infiltrate the Royal Navy in order to launch missiles at a United Nations aircraft. Gravik later meets with Talos to negotiate a parlay, but discussion breaks down when the former threatens to kill G'iah. After Talos stabs Gravik in the hand and leaves, Gravik heals his hand with the Extremis soldier's abilities. G'iah secretly sends Talos information about the attack while Fury meets with him and pleads to work together again. Fury contacts Falsworth and learns the name of the Naval Command Headquarters' officer in charge, Commodore Robert Fairbanks. Fury and Talos arrive at the HQ and interrogate Fairbanks, but the latter provokes Talos to kill him as he regresses back to a Skrull. Talos contacts G'iah, who acquires Fairbanks' authorization code, allowing them to abort the launch in time. G'iah attempts to ride off on her motorcycle, but is spotted by Gravik who suspected her of betrayal. When Gravik orders her to return to the compound, G'iah turns him down and is shot by him. Meanwhile, Priscilla secretly contacts an unknown person with Rhodes' voice wishing to speak to Gravik. She is denied.

G'iah recover from Gravik's gunshot because before she attempted to run away from the rebels, G'iah used Gravik's machine to empower herself with Extremis abilities. She and meet up with Talos, he explains to her that he is planning to ask United States President Ritson to help the Skrulls after they successfully stop the rebels, which disappoints G'iah who hoped for a stronger plan to find them a new home. Priscilla meets with Rhodes who is a Skrull named Raava in disguise and he instructs her to kill Fury. Both are unaware that Fury is listening in on their conversation. Fury later confronts Priscilla over this but they make amends after she reveals that she took an oath to her human counterpart to never harm her lover. Fury visits Rhodes and shares a drink with him to secretly give Rhodes a liquid tracker. Fury and Talos then follow him as he goes to pick up Ritson for talks with Russia. Gravik and the rebels attack Ritson's convoy disguised as Russian terrorists. Fury and Talos extract an unconscious Ritson but Talos is wounded in the process. Gravik stabs Talos in front of Fury, who leaves with Ritson.

After the failed attack on President Ritson, Pagon criticises Gravik for not killing Fury and accuses him of deceiving the other Skrulls. Gravik kills him in retaliation. Fury confronts Rhodes at the hospital, but the latter reveals that he has released the footage of Gravik killing Maria Hill as him to the public, placing Fury on a global watchlist. A group of Skrulls stage a mutiny against Gravik and attempt to kill him, but it fails and Gravik kills them all, including Beto. Fury meets up with G'iah, who reveals that Gravik is looking for something he called "The Harvest". Falsworth tracks down Dr. Rosa Dalton, a Skrull in disguise, and questions her about the DNA machine in New Skrullos. Rhodes shows Ritson pictures of New Skrullos, implicating Russia as supportive of the Skrull invasion, and advises a strike on the compound. Gravik calls Fury and offers to call off the strike if he brings him the Harvest in person. G'iah and Priscilla hold a funeral for Talos and are later ambushed by a group of Skrulls sent by Gravik. The pair successfully take down the group. In Finland, Fury leads Falsworth to a grave marked with his name, which contains the Harvest, and prepares to confront Gravik.

"Fury" confronts Gravik at New Skrullos, gives him the Harvest, and asks that he spare Earth and conquer other planets. Gravik refuses before using the Harvest to empower himself and attempt to kill Fury, only to learn it is a disguised G'iah, who also used the Harvest. The two fight, with G'iah eventually killing Gravik. Meanwhile, Raava successfully convinces Ritson to authorize a nuclear strike on New Skrullos, but is tricked by Falsworth into arranging for Ritson's evacuation. Raava attempts to retaliate, but is killed by Fury. Ritson calls off the strike, allowing G'iah to free Gravik's human prisoners, such as Ross and Rhodes. In the aftermath, Ritson issues a new bill declaring all off world species as hostile forces and threatens to hunt down the remaining Skrulls on Earth, causing unrest as civilians publicly murder various high-profile officials for fear that they are Skrulls. Falsworth meets with G'iah and proposes a partnership to protect the Skrulls against Ritson's bill. After cautioning Ritson about the unrest he caused, Fury asks Varra to come to S.A.B.E.R. with him to help negotiate at a peace summit with the Kree. She agrees and they leave Earth together.

textContent: In the TVA's headquarters, Judge Ravonna Renslayer accuses Loki of crimes against the Sacred Timeline. Loki believes the TVA should suspect The Avengers, as they went back in time, causing him to end up in this situation. However, Renslayer counters this by saying The Avengers' mission was meant to happen, but Loki's escape was not. Following this, Agent Mobius M. Mobius takes Loki to the Time Theatre to review Loki's past misdeeds and question his habit of killing and hurting people. Loki steals TVA tech to retrieve the Tesseract, but gives up escaping upon realizing that the TVA's power exceeds that of the Infinity Stones. Loki returns to the Time Theatre and witnesses a recording of the would-be future the deaths of his adoptive parents Frigga and Odin as well as his own at the hands of Thanos. Realizing that his cruelty and mischief will not lead to his ascendance, Loki agrees to work with Mobius to protect the Sacred Timeline from a rogue variant of himself.

textContent: Loki time slips to his interrogation with Mobius, who gets him to realize that most "glorious purpose" is one of burden that cannot be truly avoided, and that the best course of action is sometimes the ugliest. Loki shakes hands with Mobius before the time line spaghettified.

textContent: After returning to the TVA headquarters, Mobius convinces Ravonna Renslayer to give Loki another chance. After research, Loki proposes that The Variant is hiding in spacetime near apocalyptic events like Asgard's Ragnarok, where the impending destruction means their actions cannot change the timeline, thus concealing them from the TVA. Loki and Mobius confirm this possibility by visiting Pompeii in 79 AD than the duo then figure out that the Variant is at a hurricane in 2050 Alabama.

textContent: With Loki and Sylvie capture. Renslayer informs Mobius about Hunter C-20's death in uncertain circumstances. Mobius has them separated, punishing Loki by leaving him in a time loop with Lady Sif. After Mobius and Hunter B-15 realize they are variants after interrogating Loki and Sylvie, Mobius frees Loki from the loop, but is soon confronted by Renslayer and is pruned. Loki and Sylvie are taken to the Time Keepers by Renslayer before Hunter B-15 intervenes. In the ensuing fight, Renslayer's minutemen are killed while Renslayer is knocked unconscious by Sylvie, who destroys one of the Time Keepers, discovering they are androids. Renslayer regains consciousness and pruned Loki. Sylvie, in anger, demands the truth from Renslayer. Elsewhere, Loki awakens in an unknown realm, surrounded by other Loki variants, who invite him to come along.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie learns from Renslayer that Loki was teleported to the Void, a dimension at the end of Time where everything the TVA prunes is dumped into. Renslayer talk to an imprisoned Hunter B-15, Renslayer instructs Miss Minutes to give her the information about the TVA's founding so that she can get to whoever organized the TVA first before Loki and Sylvie could find a way.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Mobius confronts Renslayer and both accuse each other of betrayal. Renslayer leaves on a mission to find "free will" after Miss Minutes gives her information from the TVA's creator.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki Laufeyson back in the present discovers that he is uncontrollably warping across time in the TVA headquarters. Loki reunites with Mobius and warns him of the threat of the many variants of He Who Remains, the TVA's creator. Loki and Mobius M. Mobius go to meet TVA technician Ouroboros "OB", who deduces that Loki is "Time Slipping", a phenomenon possibly caused by branching timelines dangerously overloading the Temporal Loom after the death of He Who Remains. To stop Loki's time slipping, OB instructs Mobius to approach the Temporal Loom with the Temporal Aura Extractor device to extract Loki from the time stream as Loki prunes himself. Loki time slips to the future, where the TVA is being evacuated. Loki briefly encounters Sylvie Laufeydottir before he is pruned by someone at the last possible second. Mobius successfully pulls Loki from the time stream, and the two of them set out to find Sylvie, just as many TVA hunters are ordered by General Dox to search for her.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Brad under interrogation, he admits to abandoning General Dox's mission and reveals Sylvie's location. Meanwhile, O.B. attempts to repair the Loom to safely accommodate the branching timelines, but discovers he cannot access it without help from the missing Miss Minutes or He Who Remains's aura.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Casey tracks the rogue Ravonna Renslayer's TemPad on one of the remaining branching timelines, Sylvie, refusing to be involved any further, returns to back to 1982.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: At the TVA employees, the Temporal Loom reaches catastrophic failure, Loki and his allies attempt to use Timely and Ouroboros's Throughput Multiplier to fix it. It is revealed that the source of Ouroboros's knowledge is Timely himself, creating an ontological paradox. Renslayer and Miss Minutes attempt to take over the TVA, approaching the detained Wolfe, Dox and her loyalists for help. Only Brad agrees. Dox and her loyalists instead choose to be crushed to death by Miss Minutes. Wolfe prunes Hunter D-90 and kidnaps Timely. While staging a rescue, Sylvie and Loki encounter his time-slipping past self. Loki prunes his past self. Ouroboros deactivates Miss Minutes and the TVA's magic-suppressing devices. This enables Sylvie to enchant Brad, controlling him to prune Renslayer. Timely is rescued and is able to restore access to the Temporal Loom, but the Loom's increased temporal radiation spaghettifies him before he can launch the Throughput Multiplier. The Temporal Loom explodes, and the blast wave spreads toward Loki, Mobius, Sylvie, B-15, Casey, and Ouroboros in the TVA.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki successfully time slip himself back to moments before the Loom's destruction.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki survives the explosion, but everyone else has vanished and the TVA headquarters spaghettifies. Loki escapes as he begins time slipping again, taking him to branched timelines where his friends Mobius, Hunter B-15, Casey, and OB were reset to their original lives
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki time slips to the moment before the Temporal Loom's explosion. Loki just as Victor Timely prepares to launch the Throughput Multiplier, before he dies horrifically to spaghettification. As Ouroboros comments that they took too long to launch it, Loki repeatedly time-slips back in an attempt to hasten the Multiplier's launch, hoping to do it earlier by taking Timely from Renslayer and Miss Minutes during their interrogation. However, it is still too late. Loki decides to prepare Timely from the moment he arrived at the TVA, at which point the temporal radiation is low enough for Timely to be able to launch the Multiplier and make it back alive. As Loki and the others celebrate, Ouroboros discovers that as the Multiverse infinitely expands into countless branching timelines, the Loom is immediately overloaded. Timely calculates that the Loom will never be able to scale to accommodate the ever-expanding Multiverse. Loki slips to the moment before Sylvie kills He Who Remains
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Ravonna Renslayer and Miss Minutes travel to Chicago, 1868 to secretly drop the TVA Guidebook to a young Victor Timely, a variant of He Who Remains, who informed Miss Minutes about this plan before his death. They then travel to 1893 at the Chicago World's Fair.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki and Mobius arrive tracking Renslayer's TemPad. There, they see Timely presenting his Temporal Loom prototype. Timely then has four groups chasing him. Loki and Mobius, who want to use his aura to fix the Loom; Renslayer and Miss Minutes, who want him to take his variant's place with them at his side Sylvie, who wants to kill him to prevent his rise to power and a robber baron and his allies wanting revenge against Timely's fake invention scam. At Timely's Wisconsin laboratory, he turns Miss Minutes off after she professes romantic love for him. Renslayer, Loki, Mobius, and Sylvie arrive, with Sylvie gaining control. Sylvie allows Loki to take Timely back to the TVA. She then sends Renslayer to the Citadel at the End of Time.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Casey were Frank Morris in Alcatraz escaping with other prisoners in San Francisco.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki, Mobius, and Hunter B-15 find and capture Hunter X-05 in London, 1977 on the Sacred Timeline, where he lives as film actor "Brad Wolfe".
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie Laufeydottir enters a branched in Broxton, Oklahoma and visits a McDonald's restaurant and asked the cashier for everything.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki, Mobius and Brad travel to Oklahoma and find Sylvie working in a McDonald's. Loki tells her of their encounter in the TVA's future and asks for her assistance to figure out what would happen, but Sylvie refuses to involve herself with the organization. After Brad proclaims the group is in mortal danger, Sylvie enchants him, forcing him to reveal Dox's plan to simultaneously destroy the branching timelines with reset charges. Loki, Mobius, and Sylvie capture Dox, but her plan has largely succeeded and some of her allies have escaped.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie returns to McDonald and wish a Jack good night. Afterwards, she look over He Who Remains's TemPad in her possession.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki found Sylvie after she finished her shift at McDonald's, Loki approached her, only to discover much to his surprise and relief that Sylvie remembered everything, including the explosion. At a bar, Loki explained how everyone's lives were reset to before the TVA which Sylvie saw as a good thing as they were back in their real lives.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie witnessed her timeline spaghettifying like Victor Timely while visiting a records store and barely escaped in time using He Who Remains' TemPad.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki joins a TVA mission following an ambush by a variant of Loki in Oshkosh, Wisconsin. He wants assurance that the TVA will let him meet the Time Keepers instead of disintegrating him, but Mobius figures out that he is stalling.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Ouroboros is an failed science fiction writer and theoretical physics professor A.D. named Doug in Pasadena. Loki was able to finds Doug and enlists his help with Loki unable to control his time slipping, Doug proposes Loki gather everyone present at the explosion back together, so that their collective temporal aura can send them back to the right time and place. Loki gives Doug a TVA Handbook to allow him to build a TemPad before he time slip.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki was able to gathering everyone else to Doug's workshop. Sylvie went to help Loki. However, Doug's workshop also spaghettifies, as do Frank, Doug, Don, Willis, and Sylvie. Loki finally controls his time slipping by focusing on a person. Declaring that he can "rewrite the story".
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki time slips to Sylvie on what he should do next, believing that he should restore the Sacred Timeline in order to restore all of existence. Sylvie persuades him to preserve free will instead, leading Loki to believe that he can replace the Sacred Timeline with "something better".
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Hunter B-15 is an pediatrist named Verity Willis in New York City.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Hunter B-15 proves to TVA agents that they are variants by showing them a variant of Ravonna Renslayer who is a school vice-principal.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Mobius is an jet ski salesman named Don in Cleveland with two young  sons. Loki time slip outside of Don's house where Loki watches his friend with his sons. When Don see Loki he offered to sell him one of Don's two jet skis, and Loki recalled Mobius' fascination with jet skis and the possibility of owning them. However, Don was dubious about Loki's story about the TVA and Don being Mobius until Doug emerged from a Time Door in front of them.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie, projects an emulated memory into the captive Hunter C-20 to collect information about the Time-Keepers' location.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Loki, Mobius, and TVA agents travel to the Roxxcart superstore. The Variant ambushes them, using body possession to control TVA's Hunter B-15 and other locals. The Variant rejects Loki's offer for them to work together to overthrow the TVA's Time-Keepers. A variant reveals itself as a female version of Loki. She executes her scheme, teleporting the TVA reset charges she stole to various locations in spacetime, thus creating many new timeline branches. She teleports into a timeline, and Loki follows her.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: On the habitable moon Lamentis-1 Loki and Sylvie discover that the moon is about to be crushed by a planet. Both are unable to escape due to the TemPad having run out of power. The two sneak aboard a train bound for the Ark, a spaceship intended to evacuate Lamentis-1 in order to siphon its power and recharge the TemPad. On the train, Loki gets drunk, which causes him and Sylvie to be discovered and forced out by the guards. Loki accidentally breaks the TemPad, which forces him and Sylvie to approach the Ark on foot. During their journey, Sylvie reveals to Loki that the TVA is comprised entirely of variants, rather than being created by the Time-Keepers as Mobius claimed. Loki and Sylvie arrive at the Ark's location and fight their way through the guards, only to witness it being destroyed by a meteor, leaving them stranded.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: Sylvie tells Loki she escaped the TVA's detention as a child. The bond between Loki and Sylvie create a Nexus Event the like the TVA never seen. The TVA was able to locate the two and bring them in.
timeline: The Time Variance Authority Time Zone/Timeline

textContent: After successfully returning the Infinity Stones and Mjölnir to their original time, Steve chose to not travel back to 2023. He reunited with Peggy finally having the dance he promised her. The two later get married and made a life together.

At Camp Lehigh, Steve and Tony split up to respectively locate the Pym Particles and find the Tesseract. Before they meet up together again, Steve see Peggy Carter while Tony runs into Howard Stark. After a long conversation, Tony sees his father in a new light and, now a father himself, understands what he went through raising him. He manages to indirectly thank Howard for everything while maintaining his hidden identity before returning to the present with Steve.

The team of Tony, Steve, Scott, and Bruce review their mission objectives and disperse. Bruce encounters the Ancient One, but fails to persuade her of his predicament. The Ancient One educates Banner on the effects the Infinity Stones have on reality and possible ramifications that may result from the loss of just one. Though Bruce makes a compelling argument, ultimately he convinces her when he reveals that Stephen Strange willingly relinquished it to Thanos, realizing his actions was part of a bigger plan. The Ancient One loans Bruce the Time Stone and he promises to return it and the others once they've finished with them before departing for the Quantum Realm to rendezvous with the other Avengers. Meanwhile, Tony and Scott infiltrate Stark Tower as Loki is being taken into custody. Realizing that their present situation presents no opportunity to steal the Tesseract, Scott plants himself onto Stark's 2012 counterpart whom is transporting the Tesseract along with S.H.I.E.L.D. agents who are undercover HYDRA agent. and the past Avengers. Meanwhile, Tony saw them departs in the Mark LXXXV armor. In the lobby area, Scott causes a distraction by interfering with 2012 Stark's Arc Reactor, allowing the present Tony to secure the Tesseract. However, his attempts to exit the area, 2012 Hulk bursts into the lobby from the stairwell, and causing Tony to drop the Tesseract. In the confusion, Loki manages to retrieve the Tesseract and use its power to escape.
Loki land in the Gobi Desert with the Tesseract and is captured by the Time Variance Authority or the TVA.

Steve located the Chitauri scepter, but then encounters Brock Rumlow, Jasper Sitwell, Jack Rollins and other agents of HYDRA riding an elevator. Steve presents the ruse that he has been ordered to take the scepter, drawing suspicion from Rumlow and Sitwell. But, making uses of his future insight, Steve persuaded them by pretending to be a HYDRA agent himself. Steve, however, encounters another obstacle in the in his way his 2012 counterpart, who has mistaken him for Loki in disguise. The two fight, and are evenly matched but using his future knowledge by revealing Bucky is still alive, Steve manages to subdue his 2012 counterpart with the scepter. The team regroup, Tony and Scott admit to Steve, they botched their mission and there's no way to find the Tesseract now. However Tony gets an idea on how they could acquire both the Tesseract and more Pym Particles. Scott is given the scepter to return to the present, while Stark and Rogers travel to Camp Lehigh in 1970.

Thor and Rocket, having been able to locate Jane Foster on Asgard, set out to use a device to extract the Aether from her body. Thor, however, gets distracted at seeing his mother, knowing that she will die later that day. He manages to spend some extra time with her and she realizes he is from the future and has suffered. She gives him some encouragement and is ready to meet her fate even if it is just around the corner. Upon Rocket retrieving the Reality Stone and escaping Asgardian guards, Thor's talk with his mother gets interrupted, but he takes the chance to reclaim Mjölnir before he and Rocket return to 2023.
After, Tony Stark's funeral, Steve returned the Reality Stone and Mjölnir back to Asgard.

Rhodes and Nebula are dropped off on Morag and watch Peter Quill infiltrate the temple holding the Power Stone, both of them remarking on what a carefree idiot Quill is before knocking him out. However, aboard the Sanctuary II, Thanos plans his retrieval of the Power Stone with Gamora and Nebula when suddenly, the two Nebulas' systems start interfacing with each other. Although present Nebula is unaware, past Nebula sees what her future self is seeing. Thanos has his daughter examined and sees images of his success from the future. Past Nebula swears her loyalty to her father, and Thanos decides to use her to achieve his aims quicker than he ever thought. The retrieval of the Power Stone goes off without a hitch, but when Rhodes travels back to the present time, a malfunctioning Nebula is left to be found by Thanos and her past self, who uses Nebula's time-traveling device to travel forward in time and impersonate her future self.

Natasha and Clint are greeted on Vormir by Red Skull. Once they are informed of the sacrifice they have to make, the two are ready to sacrifice themselves for the other. The two fight as they each try to throw themselves off the building, and although Clint makes the jump Natasha saves him and ends up hanging by his hand. She convinces him to let her go, as there's no way to save her now, and she falls to her death. A devastated Barton claims the Soul Stone and returns to the present without Romanoff. Meanwhile, Nebula activates the Quantum Tunnel to allow passage for Thanos and his army to travel to 2023.
Steve Rogers returned the Orb and the Soul Stone to their respective locations after Thanos and the Black Order was defeated.

The Loki variants tell Loki that a cloud-like creature named Alioth, guards the Void and prevents anyone from escaping. In an attempt to reach Loki, Sylvie prunes herself and narrowly escapes Alioth with Mobius' help. Boastful Loki attempts to betray the other Lokis for President Loki and the Lokis with him, causing a fight to ensue while Loki and his variant allies escape. After reuniting with Loki, Sylvie proposes a plan to approach Alioth and enchant it, in hopes that it will lead them to the real mastermind behind the TVA's creation. As the Lokis head toward Alioth, Mobius uses a TemPad Sylvie stole from Renslayer to return to the TVA. Kid Loki and Alligator Loki escape while Classic Loki creates a large illusion of Asgard to distract Alioth, sacrificing himself in the process. This allows Loki and Sylvie to successfully enchant the creature and move past the Void. Noticing a citadel in the distance, the pair walk towards it.
Renslayer awakens in the Void and found by Alioth.

At the Citadel of He Who Remains. He Who Remains greets Loki and Sylvie, who are both surprised that he is "just a man". Using a TemPad to avoid Sylvie's attacks, He Who Remains reveals he can anticipate their actions because he has foreseen the past, present, and future and that he guided them to him. He also reveals that he created the TVA after several variants of himself discovered alternative universes and contacted each other in the 31st century. Several of them tried to conquer other universes, leading to a multiversal war. He Who Remains harnessed the creature Alioth to end it, isolate his timeline, and create the TVA to prevent further branches. As he has grown weary, he offers Loki and Sylvie a choice: kill him, end the singular timeline, and risk another multiversal war sparked by his variants, or succeed him in leading the TVA and managing the timeline. As the timeline begins to diverge, He Who Remains finds he can no longer anticipate the future and Sylvie tries to kill him. Loki fights her, fearing He Who Remains might be right and pleading that he wants to keep her safe. They kiss, but Sylvie uses the TemPad to send Loki back to the TVA headquarters and kills a surrendering He Who Remains, unleashing a multiverse with timelines that cannot be pruned.

Loki slips to the moment before Sylvie kills He Who Remains who tells Loki that the Loom is a fail-safe overloading it protects the Sacred Timeline by deleting the branches along with the TVA. He Who Remains suggests Loki kill Sylvie to save the Loom, which Loki rejects.
Renslayer at the Citadel brought out Miss Minutes. They both see He Who Remains' corpse as Miss Minutes reveals that she knows a secret about Renslayer.

Miss Minutes reveals that in the past, Renslayer commanded He Who Remains' army he proposed that Renslayer lead the TVA with him, then had Miss Minutes erase the memories of Renslayer and other TVA employees.

Loki transform the ruin He Who Remains'  throne into a golden one then he magically rejuvenates the dying timelines and rearranges them into a tree-like structure, committing himself to oversee the branches alone at the End of Time.
Loki watch over Mobius and Sylvie as the God of Stories.

The Guardians of the Multiverse confronted and battle Ultron. Strange and Thor bombard Ultron with a swarm of Mjolnirs, allowing T'Challa to steal the Soul Stone. Strange then summons a horde of zombies along with the zombified Scarlet Witch on Ultron before the team depart to his universe.
